rComments: Very knowledgeable, kind and funny. Take any of his classes, you won't be disappointed.

Prof Esleben is literally the best prof I have ever had in my 6 years of university at uOttawa. Such an intelligent, nice, caring, smart, resourceful, creative, and lovely human being. I've taken 2 of his classes and learned so much. His teaching methods are what universities should be all about

Obviously cares about the topics studied and makes it a class you want to pay attention to. Not a very tough grader and gives plenty of feedback to help with future assignments. Able to last outside class too and it very helpful to chat with individually.

Amazing. Super interesting course and very interactive. Written assignments, and group assignments on course material kept you involved and entertained. Funny and kind guy. Very open to helping understand feedback. Wants you to succeed.

Amazing prof, great evaluations that leave room for creativity and personal interpretation. Just do the readings and you get a pretty good understanding of the material. Definitely a bird course that was fun and interesting!

One of the most organized profs I've had. He was so passionate about teaching about German culture which made lectures really rewarding. He's not a tough grader, but he does expect thought and effort to be put into the assignments because he cares about us learning. He's really open to discussions so come prepared with questions if you have them

Great prof.  Unique in his way of teaching. Interesting material. It 's  a seminar so student do most of the talking so do your research on the concepts/terms assigned before coming to class so you can share your knowledge.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Such a great professor. And a super nice person too. Besides, looks like Jeremy Irons.

He is very interesting. You have to do a 'blog' every 1 or 2 weeks about the lecture on the course reader. It is an easy class if you take the time to do your lectures. There is no in-class exam. only the blogs and a take-home exam at the end of the session.

He is very clear. You have to go to every class because he goes through the lektions very fast, but he makes sure everything is clear. Also, you lose 1% for every class you miss. He is very funny, he makes a lot of jokes. He doesn't have office hours, but he is fast to answer questions through gmail and you can always make an appointment with him.
Excellent prof!
Great prof

Professor Esleben is fantastic.  He's kind, understanding, and has a great teaching style.  It's nice to have a prof who cares about his students, and who continues to teach at the same level of quality despite whatever is going on in his personal life.

This man, is a godsend.. I am a special student and I was lucky enough to have this amazing professor. He embraces participation and makes his courses very interesting. Incredibly nice, incredibly helpful and my favorite prof of all time. He has no equal, if you get the chance to take his course.. TAKE IT!  If you are reading this Mr. Elseben, TY!
Very interesting professor! Is willing to help his students when needed and very engaging. He makes the class fun to attend and you learn a lot. Very highly recommended
Awesome prof, makes the subject seem really interesting.
Super teacher!  He expects a lot from his students but is always willing to help if you ask.  You can tell he really cares both about teaching and the subject.
One of the most interesting, engaging, dynamic, and helpful professors at the university! ♥

Awesome professor. His teaching style is excellent. You can tell he really cares about teaching and his students. Your mark is split between homework assignments from the textbook and tests, with a written and verbal exam at the end. I would definitely recommend him for any courses in German.
Herr Esleben is clear, helpful and a great teacher all around. Best of all, he can control a rowdy class in a friendly but firm manner. HIGHLY recommended!
So cute! Very good prof, very intelligent, very nice guy. Recommend any class with him.
he's a very kind, smart prof, although he expects the students to participate to the course through the course website. which sucks.

This prof was one of the best that I've had since starting at U of O. He is very clear when it comes to teaching the material and there is never a problem with approaching him if you are having difficulty with the course work.  The workload is quite high, but as long as you stay on top of it you should be fine.  He is a very fair marker.

By far my favorite professor at Ottawa U, Jorg is an amazingly nice guy who makes sure his students understand his lessons and he goes out of his way to help you. Always cheerful and a great sense of humor I reccomend this fantastic teacher to everyone!!!!!!

I really enjoyed this course and I find that I learned a lot.  I liked the idea of doing the homework assignments instead of writing tests and exams because they made me feel that I am learning for the sake of learning.  This professor is a great pedagog, and I am looking forward to having him in future courses.

Very nice, knowledgeable and helpful. Lectures very interesting and clear. Lot of applied work in class which is good. However, ridiculously huge workload. It is necessary for learning a new language, but make sure you keep on top of your work, don't miss 1 class & don't take this class if looking for a free ride (unless you speak the language!)
Very good prof. Made learning fun.

He is kind, reasonable and upbeat. He seems to enjoy teaching and cares about how the students are doing. The class involved a lot of independent, self-directed learning, yet managed to convey a lot of interesting material. I highly recommend!

Prof Esleben is helpful and friendly, able to bring any subject he teaches to life.  However, because the class used a class discussion format, it was often difficult to prepare for tests.  But as long as you're keen on self-directed learning, he's a FANTASTIC prof.
Great professor, great class
Cool guy, makes lessons easy to understand, doesn't care about lateness, generally a generous marker.
Too much whistling!  Seriously!
He's a good prof, really hot too.
Very Kind, Very Helpful
